%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inflation%20is%20scrambling%20Americans'%20perceptions%20of%20middle%20class%20life%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221912%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20dollar%20bill%20with%20glitch%20effect%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6631113610dfcda40964deb6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22956%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Raines%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMany%20Americans%20have%20come%20to%20feel%20that%20a%20middle-class%20lifestyle%20is%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBlame%20inflation%20for%20bringing%20down%20the%20mood%20and%20making%20the%20economy%20seem%20much%20worse%20than%20it%20is.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMoney%20experts%20say%20people%20feeling%20downbeat%20can%20create%20a%20financial%20plan%20to%20alleviate%20stress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EVincent%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20medical%20sales%20rep%2C%20makes%20%24130%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20dream%20when%20he%20was%20younger%20%E2%80%94%20once%20he%20was%20making%20six%20figures%2C%20he%20assumed%20he'd%20be%20in%20financial%20nirvana%2C%20worry-free%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffewer-americans-taking-time-off-for-vacation-because-of-inflation-2023-7%5C%22%3Eoff%20on%20vacation%20somewhere%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20once%20a%20year%2C%20perhaps%20able%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20in%20the%20not-too-distant%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20if%20I%20could%20make%20six%20figures%2C%20I'd%20have%20a%20nice%20life.%20I%20can%20save%20up%20the%20down%20payment%20on%20a%20home%20and%20start%20to%20begin%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Vincent%2C%20who%20preferred%20to%20only%20use%20his%20first%20name%20to%20protect%20his%20privacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20surprised%20to%20find%20out%20that%20in%20Santa%20Barbara%2C%20a%20coastal%20California%20city%20where%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.erieri.com%2Fcost-of-living%2Funited-states%2Fcalifornia%2Fsanta-barbara%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20living%20is%2065%25%20higher%20than%20the%20national%20average%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he's%20barely%20able%20to%20save%20for%20anything%2C%20let%20alone%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20plan%20for%20kids%2C%20or%20hit%20other%20milestones%20of%20middle-class%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBigger%20ticket%20items%20that%20our%20parents%20could%20have%20bought%2C%20like%20a%20home%20or%20car%2C%20that%20is%2C%20just%20to%20me%2C%20out%20of%20reach%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Vincent%2C%20though%20he%20acknowledged%20his%20budget%20could%20go%20further%20in%20a%20city%20with%20a%20lower%20cost%20of%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20have%20to%20save%2010k%20for%20six%20or%20seven%20years%20straight%20and%20really%20sacrifice%20to%20put%20down%20on%20maybe%20the%20dumpiest%20thing%20I%20could%20find%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVincent's%20experience%20is%20emblematic%20of%20what%20has%20become%20of%20the%20middle-class%20American%20dream%2C%20with%20many%20earning%20well%20into%20six%20figures%20but%20feeling%20like%20they're%20way%20behind%20the%20curve%20or%20that%20the%20economic%20chips%20are%20stacked%20against%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20these%20concerns%20are%20real%20%E2%80%94%20see%20the%20wildly%20expensive%20US%20housing%20market%20%E2%80%94%20while%20others%2C%20experts%20say%2C%20may%20be%20a%20matter%20of%20perception%20versus%20reality%2C%20as%20the%20economy%20feels%20tough%20even%20as%20earnings%20are%20growing%20and%20employment%20is%20strong.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVincent%20is%20among%20a%20growing%20group%20of%20middle-class%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20most%20recently%20defined%20in%202022%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2020%2F07%2F23%2Fare-you-in-the-american-middle-class%2F%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20households%20earning%20between%20%2448%2C500%20and%20%24145%2C500%20%E2%80%94%20who%20don't%20feel%20they%20can't%20afford%20to%20live%20a%20traditional%20middle-class%20life%2C%20replete%20with%20a%20home%20and%20a%20comfortable%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Eoin%20Sheehan%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20analyst%20at%20Redfield%20%26amp%3B%20Wilton%2C%20inflation%20has%20caused%20many%20Americans%20to%20ignore%20the%20overall%20strength%20of%20the%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowth%2C%20hiring%2C%20and%20financial%20markets%20are%20strong%2C%20while%20wage%20growth%20has%20started%20to%20exceed%20the%20pace%20of%20inflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22718%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wage%20growth%20has%20started%20to%20beat%20the%20pace%20of%20inflation.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663133aa10dfcda40964f7b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWage%20growth%20has%20started%20to%20beat%20the%20pace%20of%20inflation.%3Cp%3EFederal%20Reserve%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20higher%20costs%20pose%20challenges%20to%20retiring%20or%20buying%20a%20home%2C%20those%20goals%20aren't%20out%20of%20reach%20with%20careful%20planning%2C%20according%20to%20Chris%20Collins%2C%20a%20wealth%20advisor%20at%20Northwestern%20Mutual's%20Collins%20Financial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollins%20suspects%20that%20most%20middle-class%20Americans%20feel%20anxious%20about%20their%20financial%20situation%20due%20to%20financial%20shock%20fatigue%20%E2%80%94%20the%20exhaustion%20of%20navigating%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-outlook-pandemic-stock-market-crash-inflation-recession-rates-ai-2024-2%5C%22%3Ebig%20economic%20shock%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20another%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20a%20lack%20of%20financial%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20clients%20typically%20start%20to%20calm%20down%20once%20they%20crunch%20the%20numbers%20and%20figure%20out%20how%20much%20they%20need%20to%20save%20for%20retirement%20or%20meet%20their%20other%20financial%20goals.%20Prior%20to%20that%2C%20many%20falsely%20assumed%20they%20needed%20to%20work%20forever%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20telling%20people%2C%20'You%20are%20going%20to%20die%20broken%20and%20alone.'%20It's%2C%20'Hey%2C%20with%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20work%20here%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20all%20right%2C'%26quot%3B%20Collins%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20feel%20like%20they%20can%20relax%20until%20somebody%20runs%20the%20financial%20plan%2C%20runs%20the%20modeling%20and%20says%2C%20'you're%20going%20to%20be%20fine.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20those%20statements%20don't%20square%20with%20how%20many%20households%20may%20be%20feeling%20about%20their%20financial%20and%20wealth%20status.%20The%20sentiment%20is%20all%20over%20the%20place%20online%2C%20expressed%20by%20social%20media%20users%20who%20identify%20as%20middle%20class%20but%20say%20they're%20increasingly%20feeling%20less%20well-off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20user%20Jessica%20in%20Alabama%20said%20she%20believed%20the%20middle%20class%20was%20dying.%20She%20pointed%20to%20her%20eldest%20daughter%2C%20who%20she%20says%20worked%2060%20hours%20a%20week%20during%20her%20pregnancy%20to%20provide%20for%20her%20family.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20we%20even%20have%20a%20middle%20class%20anymore%2C%20or%20is%20it%20just%20the%20haves%20and%20the%20have-nots%3F%26quot%3B%20Jessica%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40that1crazy72%2Fvideo%2F7337800449371737387%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20post%20in%20February.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20the%20haves%20are%20having%2C%20and%20the%20have-nots%20are%20struggling.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20sorry%2C%20but%20if%20you%20know%20somebody%20with%20kids%20and%20they%20say%20they're%20not%20struggling%20financially%2C%20they're%20lying%2C%26quot%3B%20Kayla%2C%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40professionalgirlmama%2Fvideo%2F7331840391639076138%5C%22%3ETikTok%20user%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%20She%20pointed%20to%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20groceries%20and%20other%20essentials.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHonestly%2C%20life%20is%20difficult%20for%20the%20middle%20class%2C%26quot%3B%20Vincent%20added.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I%20can%20make%20ends%20meet%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20really%20move%20this%20lifestyle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3ECost-of-living%20crisis%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMiddle-class%20Americans%20have%20been%20feeling%20worse%20about%20the%20economy%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20but%20the%20negative%20mood%20appears%20to%20have%20ticked%20up%20sharply%20in%20recent%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20anxiety%20has%20hit%20an%20all-time%20high%2C%20according%20to%20a%20survey%20from%20Northwestern%20Mutual%2C%20and%20a%20survey%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.primerica.com%2Fpublic%2FFact_Sheet_Primerica_Financial_Security_Monitor_Q1_2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPrimerica%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20half%20of%20middle-class%20households%20say%20their%20financial%20situation%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20so%20good%26quot%3B%20or%20outright%20%26quot%3Bpoor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20in%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20inflation%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20feeling.%2051%25%20of%20respondents%20in%20the%20Northwestern%20Mutual%20survey%20said%20inflation%20was%20the%20biggest%20obstacle%20to%20financial%20security%2C%20while%2067%25%20of%20households%20in%20Primerica's%20survey%20said%20their%20income%20was%20falling%20behind%20the%20cost%20of%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20making%20people%20feel%20locked%20out%20of%20many%20of%20the%20milestones%20long%20associated%20with%20middle-class%20life.%2074%25%20of%20middle%20class%20Americans%20have%20cut%20back%20on%20non-essential%20spending%2C%20according%20to%20Primerica's%20survey.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fno-summer-vacation-youre-not-alone-1810133%5C%22%3EA%20full%20half%20of%20Americans%20surveyed%20said%20they%20didn't%20plan%20on%20going%20on%20a%20summer%20vacation%3C%2Fa%3E%20due%20to%20a%20higher%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20according%20to%20a%202023%20Redfield%20%26amp%3B%20Wilton%20survey%20conducted%20for%20Newsweek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20are%20also%20dipping%20into%20their%20savings%2C%20making%20retirement%20feel%20uncertain.%2060%25%20of%20Americans%20say%20they%20don't%20think%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-pensions-student-loan-debt-2024-3%5C%22%3Esaving%20enough%20to%20comfortably%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Primerica.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E46%25%20of%20middle-class%20Americans%20said%20they've%20dialed%20back%20or%20completely%20paused%20saving%20for%20the%20future%20and%2038%25%20said%20they%20didn't%20think%20they%20could%20afford%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%3Eunexpected%20expense%20over%20%241000%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20anxieties%20about%20things%20like%20owning%20their%20own%20home%2C%20going%20to%20college%20%E2%80%94%20all%20these%20things%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20Americans%20perceive%20as%20being%20sort%20of%20indicators%20of%20middle-class%20status%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20them%20now%20don't%20think%20those%20things%20are%20attainable%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Sheehan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuying%20a%20home%20may%20be%20the%20greatest%20example%20of%20a%20tenet%20of%20middle-class%20life%20feeling%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20many%2C%20and%20that%20struggle%20is%20very%20real%20rather%20than%20merely%20negatively%20perceived.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20mortgage%20rates%20hovering%20close%20to%20a%2023-year-high%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3