this%20stress%2C%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnemesrush.com%2Fabout%2Fteam%2Fjustin-rush%2F%5C%22%3EJustin%20Rush%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcfp%5C%22%3Ecertified%20financial%20planner%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20specializes%20in%20tailoring%20his%20clients'%20financial%20plans%20to%20their%20unique%20needs.%20I%20told%20Rush%20about%20your%20situation%20and%20asked%20how%20he%20would%20advise%20you%20to%20financially%20navigate%20this%20transition%20from%20half%20of%20a%20couple%20to%20a%20single%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERush%20responded%20with%20a%20wealth%20of%20great%20ideas%20for%20minimizing%20your%20tax%20liabilities%20and%20maximizing%20your%20nest%20egg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20Rush%20tackled%20the%20question%20of%20your%20recently%20increased%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-tax-liability%5C%22%3Etax%20liability%3C%2Fa%3E.%20No%20longer%20filing%20jointly%20means%20your%20income%20automatically%20gets%20pushed%20into%20higher%20brackets%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20costly%20adjustment.%20The%20good%20news%20is%20that%20Rush%20says%20you%20can%20avoid%20this%20adjustment%20by%20filing%20your%20taxes%20as%20a%20qualifying%20widow%20for%20two%20years%20after%20your%20wife's%20death.%20By%20filing%20as%20a%20qualifying%20widow%2C%20you%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20same%20tax%20brackets%20you%20were%20in%20when%20you%20filed%20jointly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERush%20also%20mentioned%20charitable%20donations%20as%20a%20means%20people%20often%20use%20to%20achieve%20a%20higher%20tax%20benefit.%20If%20you%20have%20been%20donating%20to%20charity%20over%20the%20years%2C%20lumping%20these%20charitable%20contributions%20together%20will%20allow%20you%20to%20itemize%20them%20versus%20taking%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-standard-deduction-irs-taxes%5C%22%3Estandard%20deduction%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20increasing%20your%20tax%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20tax%20strategy%20Rush%20suggested%20is%20moving%20your%20nest%20egg%20from%20CDs%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbonds-vs-cds%5C%22%3Emunicipal%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Municipal%20bonds%20are%20backed%20by%20local%20taxes%20and%20projects.%20Rush%20likes%20municipal%20bonds%20because%20their%20interest%20is%20triple-protected%20from%20city%2C%20state%2C%20and%20federal%20taxes%2C%20and%20are%2C%20therefore%2C%20tax-free.%20While%20municipal%20bonds%20have%20lower%20interest%20rates%20than%20CDs%2C%20the%20amount%20you%20will%20save%20by%20not%20having%20your%20interest%20taxed%20may%20be%20worth%20the%20switch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20your%20nest%20egg%2C%20Rush%20asked%20about%20your%20risk%20tolerance.%20If%20you%20are%20comfortable%20exposing%20your%20savings%20to%20stocks%2C%20dividend-paying%20stocks%20have%20a%20better%20tax%20rate%20than%20ordinary%20income%20and%20could%20be%20your%20best%20bet%20for%20making%20your%20money%20work%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20asked%20Rush%20about%20the%20remainder%20of%20your%20car%20loan.%20I%20wondered%20if%20you'd%20be%20better%20off%20just%20wiping%20it%20out%20now.%20He%20felt%20you%20should%20likely%20keep%20doing%20what%20you're%20doing%2C%20although%20this%20depends%20on%20the%20interest%20rate%20on%20the%20car%20loan.%20As%20long%20as%20it%20is%20lower%20than%20the%20interest%20rates%20on%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%5C%22%3Einvestments%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you're%20right%20to%20continue%20making%20payments%20on%20it.%20However%2C%20he%20added%20the%20caveat%20that%20sometimes%2C%20from%20an%20emotional%20standpoint%2C%20eliminating%20as%20many%20monthly%20payments%20as%20possible%20can%20create%20a%20sense%20of%20security%20worth%20the%20financial%20trade-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELearning%20how%20to%20li