7d9b810dfcda409623009%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22767%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESen.%20Martin%20Heinrich%20speaks%20with%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20during%20a%20break%20as%20the%20Senate%20held%20an%20AI%20forum%20with%20industry%20leaders%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EBill%20O'Leary%2FThe%20Washington%20Post%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20AI-policy%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20they're%20not%20completely%20against%20setting%20federal%20regulations%20on%20artificial%20intelligence%20as%20long%20as%20it%20won't%20cripple%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20experts%2C%20like%20Rebecca%20Finlay%2C%20who%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20non-profit%20organization%20called%20Partnership%20on%20AI%2C%20said%20that%20regulations%20are%20necessary%20to%20further%20innovation.%20Finlay's%20nonprofit%20is%20focused%20on%20responsibly%20promoting%20the%20development%20and%20regulation%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20very%20clear%20that%20you%20need%20to%20have%20regulation%20in%20place%20in%20order%20to%20advance%20innovation%2C%26quot%3B%20Finlay%20said.%20%26quot%3BClear%20rules%20of%20the%20road%20allow%20for%20more%20companies%20to%20be%20more%20competitive%20in%20being%20more%20innovative%20to%20do%20the%20work%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20if%20we're%20really%20going%20to%20take%20the%20benefits%20of%20AI.%20One%20of%20the%20things%20that%20we%20are%20advocating%20strongly%20for%20is%20a%20level%20of%20transparency%20with%20regard%20to%20how%20these%20systems%20are%20being%20built%20and%20developed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20she%20doesn't%20think%20there's%20a%20right%20or%20wrong%20decision%20between%20developing%20open%20or%20closed-source%20AI%20tools%20%E2%80%94%20she%20said%20she's%20seen%20%26quot%3Bharms%26quot%3B%20from%20both%20types%20%E2%80%94%20as%20long%20as%20they're%20both%20developed%20responsibly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRather%20than%20arguing%20between%20a%20binary%20choice%20between%20open%20and%20closed%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20really%20core%20that%20we%20hold%20all%20model%20developers%20and%20deployers%20accountable%20for%20ensuring%20that%20their%20models%20are%20developed%20as%20safely%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Zhang%2C%20the%20senior%20manager%20for%20policy%20initiatives%20at%20the%20Stanford%20Institute%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhai.stanford.edu%2Fnews%2Fhow-promote-responsible-open-foundation-models%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHuman-Centered%20Artificial%20Intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20echoed%20Finlay's%20hope%20that%20regulations%20don't%20stifle%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20the%20governance%20around%20open%20foundation%20models%20are%2C%20for%20the%20long%20term%2C%20beneficial%20for%20opening%20innovation%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20too-early%20restrict%20the%20development%20of%20open%20innovation%20that%20academia%2C%20for%20example%2C%20academic%20institutions%20thrive%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20are%20the%20challenges%20of%20crafting%20AI%20regulation%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chuck%20schumer%20smiles%20whiles%20amy%20klobuchar%20whispers%20into%20his%20ear%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6627c20a0dfb1341e9fddfc6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20median%20age%20of%20the%20Senate%20is%20over%2065%20years%20old%2C%20and%20lawmakers%20are%20having%20a%20difficult%20time%20hiring%20AI%20experts%20to%20their%20offices%2C%20who%20are%20mostly%20choosing%20to%20work%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%3Cp%3EDrew%20Angerer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20hurdles%20that%20legislators%20face%20in%20regulating%20AI%2C%20Finlay%20said%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bjust%20keeping%20up%20to%20the%20state%20of%20the%20science%20and%20the%20technology%20as%20it%20is%20developed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it's%20difficult%20for%20lawmakers%20to%20draft%20regulations%20because%20most%20AI%20companies%20develop%20their%20models%20not%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bpublicly%20funded%20research%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20they%20do%20so%20privately%20until%20they%20choose%20to%20share%20their%20advancements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ideal%20solution%20would%20be%20to%20empower%20some%20kind%20of%20office%20or%20regulator%20to%20update%20the%20laws%20as%20they%20go%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Green-Lowe%2C%20from%20the%20Center%20for%20AI%20Policy%2C%20said%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20the%20easiest%20thing%20to%20accomplish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20also%20in%20a%20moment%20where%20people%20are%20very%20concerned%20about%20overreach%20from%20executive%20power%20and%20about%20the%20proper%20role%20of%20bureaucracies%20or%20the%20civil%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20Green-Lowe%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20there%20are%20people%20in%20Congress%20who%20are%20skeptical%20that%20Congress%20can%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20changes%20in%20technology%2C%20but%20also%20skeptical%20that%20the%20power%20to%20do%20so%20should%20be%20delegated%20to%20an%20agency.%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20failing%20to%20implement%20a%20formal%20way%20of%20regulating%20the%20sector%20would%20effectively%20let%20companies%20play%20by%20their%20own%20rules%2C%20something%20he%20and%20the%20Center%20for%20AI%20Policy%20don't%20purport%20to%20be%20the%20best%20course%20of%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20challenge%20comes%20from%20AI%20experts%20and%20researchers%20choosing%20private%20sector%20jobs%20instead%20of%20ones%20in%20the%20government%2C%20a%20kind%20of%20%26quot%3Bbrain%20drain%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20new%20AI%20Ph.D.'s%20that%20graduate%20in%20North%20America%20go%20to%20private%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20citing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faiindex.stanford.edu%2Freport%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanford's%202024%20AI%20Index%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BLess%20than%2040%25%20go%20to%20government%20looking%20to%20create%20all%20those%20AI%20regulations%20and%20governance%20structures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22744%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Where%20AI%20PhD's%20go%20after%20receiving%20their%20degrees%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6627dfc00dfb1341e9fe054f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22771%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20AI%20experts%20end%20up%20working%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20rather%20than%20for%20universities%20or%20federal%20governments.%3Cp%3EStanford's%20Institute%20for%20Human-Centered%20AI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELacking%20staffers%20who%20can%20fully%20understand%20the%20complexity%20of%20AI%20and%20its%20future%20puts%20more%20onus%20on%20an%20aging%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcongress-oldest-history-gerontocracy-lawmakers-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20US%20Congress%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20regulate%20the%20far-reaching%20tech%2C%20a%20difficult%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhang%20said%20there's%20also%20a%20common%20misconception%20that%20working%20in%20government%20provides%20less%20access%20to%20money%20than%20working%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20a%20hundred%20percent%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20governments%20to%20appeal%20to%20those%20technical%20students%2C%20I%20think%20they%20just%20need%20to%20highlight%20the%20public%20service%20aspect%20and%20then%20give%20them%20the%20resources%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fostp%2Fnews-updates%2F2024%2F01%2F29%2Fa-call-to-service-for-ai-talent-in-the-federal-government%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBiden%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20a%20%26quot%3Bcall%20to%20service%26quot%3B%20aimed%20at%20solving%20this%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20calling%20on%20AI%20and%20AI-enabling%20experts%20to%20join%20us%20to%20advance%20this%20research%20and%20ensure%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20AI%20models%20is%20safe%2C%20secure%2C%20and%20trustworthy%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20administration%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-regulations-what-lawmakers-president-are-doing-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714908541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6627c4c610dfcda40962130c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-regulations-what-lawmakers-president-are-doing-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lawmakers%20are%20struggling%20to%20regulate%20AI%20because%20the%20technology%20is%20developing%20at%20a%20rapid%20speed%20and%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20expertise%20to%20keep%20up.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mhall%40businessinsider.com%20(Madison%20Hall)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-regulations-what-lawmakers-president-are-doing-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kangana%20Ranaut%20Attacks%20Tejasvi%20Surya%20Mistaking%20Him%20For%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EActor-turned-politician%20Kangana%20Ranaut%20intended%20to%20target%20an%20opposition%20leader%20but%20mistakenly%20ended%20up%20attacking%20her%20BJP%20colleague%20instead.%20A%20similarity%20in%20names%20-%20Tejashwi%20and%20Tejasvi%20-%20was%20behind%20Ms%20Ranaut's%20fumble.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20party%20of%20spoilt%20prin