0chances.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Zers%20who%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hit-hardest-pandemic-jobs-dating-education-depression-lockdown-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20hit%20adolescence%20during%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20especially%20vulnerable%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dallasfed.org%2Fcd%2Fcommunities%2F2023%2F2303%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Dallas%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-loneliness-does-to-the-body-and-brain-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELoneliness%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-job-market-unemployment-rate-economy-career-news-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etough%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20leaving%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20feeling%20stuck%2C%20isolated%2C%20and%20unsupported.%20In%20fact%2C%20they're%20members%20of%20the%20disconnected%20youth%20%E2%80%94%20defined%20as%20Gen%20Zers%20who%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-increasingly-no-income-cannot-retire-or-buy-houses-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20in%20school%20and%20not%20working%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20have%20disenrolled%20or%20taken%20a%20break%20from%20school%2C%20while%20others%20have%20graduated%20but%20aren't%20employed.%20Nearly%204.7%20million%20young%20people%20were%20disconnected%20in%202021%2C%20according%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eresearch%20firm%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.measureofamerica.org%2FDYinteractive%2F%23National%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeasure%20of%20America%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20of%20these%20Gen%20Zers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisconnected-youth-a-tale-of-2-gen-zs-in-america-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they're%20actively%20looking%20for%20work%20but%20live%20in%20lower-opportunity%20areas%20where%20jobs%20are%20sparse%2C%20adult%20support%20is%20limited%2C%20and%20mental%20health%20resources%20are%20few%20and%20far%20between.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20these%20stepping%20stones%20that%20are%20quite%20difficult%2C%20quite%20slippery%2C%20but%20some%20people%20have%20someone%20on%20each%20side%20helping%20them%20across%20those%20stepping%20stones%2C%26quot%3B%20Reeves%20said.%20%26quot%3BOthers%20are%20supposed%20to%20do%20it%20on%20their%20own.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisconnected%20youth%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20long-term%20stagnation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Gen%20Zers%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewho%20are%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2012%20and%2027%20%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eare%20in%20this%20decisive%20decade.%20For%20young%20people%20in%20this%20age%20group%2C%20their%20living%20circumstances%20have%20major%20implications%20for%20their%20long-term%20health%2C%20happiness%2C%20and%20economic%20stability%2C%20the%20Brookings%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20analyzed%20education%20and%20employment%20benchmarks%20for%20Americans%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2014%20and%2024%20based%20on%20data%20pulled%20from%20the%202015-2019%20Annual%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Supplement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20benchmarks%20included%20enrollment%20in%209th%20grade%20with%20a%202.0%20GPA%20or%20higher%2C%20high%20school%20graduation%20with%20a%202.0%20GPA%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eor%20higher%2C%20college%20enrollment%20or%20full-time%20employment%20three%20years%20after%20graduating%20from%20high%20school%2C%20and%20enrollment%20or%20work%20at%20the%20age%20of%2024.%20The%20researchers%20chose%20to%20stop%20their%20analysis%20in%202019%20since%20the%20pandemic%20disrupted%20enrollment%2C%20work%2C%20and%20living%20arrangement%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20shows%20that%20just%2060%25%20of%20young%20adults%20met%20these%20four%20milestone%20indicators.%20Brookings%20researchers%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethis%20has%20much%20to%20do%20with%20their%20family%20income%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20young%20people%20living%20in%20higher-opportunity%20areas%20during%20their%20teenage%20years%20might%20have%20better%20upward%20mobility%20as%20adults.%20Researchers%20said%20they%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20enroll%20in%20higher%20education%20and%20land%20better-paying%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%2021%2C%20Brookings%20found%20that%2094%25%20of%20those%20in%20the%20highest%20socioeconomic%20group%20%E2%80%94%20defined%20as%20the%20top%20quintile%20of%20income-earning%20households%20%E2%80%94%20are%20enrolled%20in%20school%20or%20working%2C%20compared%20to%2078%25%20for%20the%20lowest%20socioeconomic%20group%2C%20including%20the%20lowest%20quintile%20households.%20By%20the%20time%20young%20adults%20turn%2024%2C%20just%2031%25%20have%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20higher%2C%20while%2058%25%20work%20full%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20education%20gap%20impacts%20future%20income%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Fprograms%2Fcoe%2Findicator%2Fcba%2Fannual-earnings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Center%20for%20Education%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%20data%20shows%20that%2025-to-34-year-olds%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20earned%20%2461%2C600%20a%20year%2C%20compared%20to%20%2439%2C700%20for%20those%20with%20just%20a%20high%20school%20diploma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20also%20said%20gender%2C%20race%2C%20and%20family%20circumstances%20shape%20young%20Americans'%20financial%20futures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20half%20of%20Black%20young%20adults%20work%20full-time%2C%20compared%20to%2062%25%20of%20white%20young%20adults%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Black%2C%20Hispanic%2C%20and%20Asian%20students%20have%20lower%20rates%20of%20school%20enrollment%20and%20employment%20than%20white%20students.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20young%20women%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20employed%20by%20age%2024%20than%20young%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20said%20isolation%20is%20another%20contributor%20to%20the%20disconnected%20youth%20phenomenon.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-living-with-parents-save-money-housing-crisis-cost-2024-2%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNow%2520more%2520than%2520half%2520of%2Cstarts%2520with%2520the%2520housing%2520market.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMore%20Gen%20Zers%20live%20at%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20previous%20generations%2C%20and%20many%20are%20experiencing%20higher%20levels%20of%20loneliness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldhappiness.report%2Fed%2F2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Happiness%20Report%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20that%20young%20Americans%20are%20overall%20not%20satisfied%20with%20their%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20young%20adults%20in%20North%20America%20reported%20some%20of%20the%20lowest%20levels%20of%20life%20satisfaction%20in%20years%2C%20ranking%2062nd%20out%20of%20143%20countries%20for%20this%20age%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisconnected%20youth%20are%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20disability%2C%20homelessness%2C%20substance%20abuse%2C%20and%20involvement%20with%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%2C%20per%20the%20Brookings%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20help%20disconnected%20youth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20many%20disconnected%20youth%20struggle%20with%20school%20and%20work%2C%20researchers%20cautioned%20against%20a%20%26quot%3Bone%20size%20fits%20all%26quot%3B%20solution.%20Reeves%20said%20there%20are%20many%20paths%20toward%20success%20for%20young%20people%20%E2%80%94%20not%20every%20student%20will%20succeed%20in%20the%20same%20higher%20education%20or%20career%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20quite%20clear%20from%20this%20that%20there%20both%20is%20not%20and%20should%20not%20be%20one%20narrow%20track%20to%20success%2C%20but%20we%20should%20think%20in%20terms%20of%20opportunity%20pluralism%2C%26quot%3B%20Reeves%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Zaff%2C%20a%20research%20professor%20in%20applied%20human%20development%20at%20Boston%20University%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20the%20key%20to%20helping%20young%20Americans%20is%20building%20adult%20mentorship%20networks%20that%20provide%20Gen%20Zers%20with%20opportunities.%20He%20also%20suggested%20schools%20invest%20in%20lifting%20students'%20financial%20and%20mental%20burdens%2C%20such%20as%20providing%20free%20or%20reduced%20lunch%20and%20bus%20fares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20schools%20are%20already%20taking%20steps%20to%20help%20students%20be%20more%20social%20and%20engaged%2C%20including%20investing%20in%20mentorship%20and%20peer-support%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIan%20Rowe%2C%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20nonprofit%20policy%20research%20firm%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20said%20that%20at%20his%20Bronx-based%20Vertex%20Partnership%20Academies%2C%20students%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bpastoral%20connection%26quot%3B%20three%20times%20a%20day%20with%20a%20teacher%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewho%20connects%20with%20students%20beyond%20lessons.%20He%20said%20his%20school%20also%20restricts%20phones%20and%20AirPods%20during%20the%20day%20so%20students%20can%20better%20connect%20with%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20avoid%20talking%20to%20strangers%20even%20though%20it%20makes%20them%20happy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lara%20Aknin%2C%20an%20editor%20at%20the%20World%20Happiness%20Report.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20gain%20so%20much%20intimacy%2C%20warmth%2C%20and%20happiness%20from%20having%20deep%20conversations%20with%20others%2C%20but%20we%20shy%20away%20from%20doing%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20suggested%20using%20study%20groups%20in%20schools%20to%20foster%20more%20regular%2C%20in-person%20contact%20between%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZaff%20added%20that%20young%20adults%20need%20scaffolding%20to%20stay%20connected%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that%20means%20having%20people%20at%20school%20to%20help%20them%20fill%20out%20a%20FAFSA%20form%20or%20being%20offered%20apprenticeship%20opportunities%20in%20high%20school.%20He%20said%20that%20adults%20are%20important%20in%20supporting%20young%20people%20as%20they%20make%20decisions%20about%20their%20lives%20and%20futures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20young%20people%20feel%20empowered%20to%20exact%20the%20agency%20that%20we%20know%20they%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Zaff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20Gen%20Zer%20who%20isn't%20employed%20or%20enrolled%20in%20school%3F%20Are%20you%20a%20parent%20of%20disconnected%20youths%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aallisonkelly%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eallisonkelly%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ensheidlower%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-zers-disconnected-youth-leaving-school-work-unemployed-feeling-unhappy-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714903681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66313f4410dfcda40964fd7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-zers-disconnected-youth-leaving-school-work-unemployed-feeling-unhappy-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2014%20and%2024%20are%20in%20their%20decisive%20decade.%20Many%20of%20them%20are%20dropping%20out%20of%20school%20and%20feeling%20financially%20unstable.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40insider.com%20(Alli